destroyed in him lives on in me.

1456
01:18:41,675 --> 01:18:47,222
Like a nuclear blast...
that never burns out.

1457
01:18:51,602 --> 01:18:52,603
Monster?

1458
01:18:53,395 --> 01:18:55,230
I'm good.

1459
01:18:56,231 --> 01:18:58,525
<i>Hey, Runners.</i>

1460
01:18:58,609 --> 01:19:02,029
<i>You can't outrun Fate.
And you cannot hide...</i>

1461
01:19:02,696 --> 01:19:04,198
<i>from Destiny.</i>

1462
01:19:04,281 --> 01:19:05,574
That's actually not true.

1463
01:19:09,828 --> 01:19:12,289
Before he was killed, Dad
refurbed this Cold War shelter

1464
01:19:12,373 --> 01:19:13,832
he found in a nearby forest.

1465
01:19:13,916 --> 01:19:16,085
I have a detailed map
for how to get there.

1466
01:19:16,168 --> 01:19:17,812
You could survive down
there for three years.

1467
01:19:17,836 --> 01:19:19,713
But you'll only need
it for two weeks.

1468
01:19:19,797 --> 01:19:22,174
We'll pre-shoot the rest
of your tapes tomorrow.

1469
01:19:22,800 --> 01:19:23,800
What do you think?

1470
01:19:24,510 --> 01:19:25,427
Um...

1471
01:19:25,511 --> 01:19:26,553
Or...

1472
01:19:28,055 --> 01:19:30,265
Maybe just... white.

1473
01:19:32,768 --> 01:19:34,269
Hardcore.

1474
01:19:34,353 --> 01:19:35,354
Check this out.

1475
01:19:36,814 --> 01:19:40,734
You can be arrested just for
having <i>The Truth</i> in your house.

1476
01:19:40,818 --> 01:19:43,737
So these won't be distributed
until right after you win.

1477
01:19:44,321 --> 01:19:45,531
What the hell?

1478
01:19:45,614 --> 01:19:48,450
It's a special issue on the
Network's most heinous crimes.

1479
01:19:48,534 --> 01:19:50,077
What does that have to do with me?

1480
01:19:50,160 --> 01:19:52,371
A bomb's chemicals
hold great power.

1481
01:19:52,454 --> 01:19:56,125
But without an initiator to
make it go boom, it's harmless.

1482
01:19:56,208 --> 01:19:59,753
You know why they cheered for you
down there? They think you just might win.

1483
01:19:59,837 --> 01:20:02,923
And if you can survive against
those Goons, so can they.

1484
01:20:03,007 --> 01:20:04,800
The people have had it.

1485
01:20:04,883 --> 01:20:08,762
This country's ready to
blow... and you're the initiator.

1486
01:20:08,846 --> 01:20:11,140
I'm not the initiator!

1487
01:20:12,349 --> 01:20:14,601
I'm a guy trying to
get back to his family.

1488
01:20:14,685 --> 01:20:17,479
It's you against the
world either way, brother.

1489
01:20:17,563 --> 01:20:19,106
Why not be both?

1490
01:20:25,988 --> 01:20:26,989
Come on.

1491
01:20:32,202 --> 01:20:35,831
My mom thinks the bathroom across
the hall is haunted, so that's all you.

1492
01:20:36,665 --> 01:20:39,752
If the light in the hallway
is off, she's asleep.

1493
01:20:40,544 --> 01:20:42,129
Hey.

1494
01:20:43,756 --> 01:20:44,996
I appreciate what you're doing.

1495
01:20:45,799 --> 01:20:49,053
But if they find out you helped me,
those same Goons that got your dad...

1496
01:20:50,179 --> 01:20:52,014
they'll come for you.

1497
01:20:52,097 --> 01:20:53,390
One can hope.

1498
01:20:58,270 --> 01:20:59,605
<i>This message is for Cathy.</i>

1499
01:21:01,148 --> 01:21:02,649
<i>In case you see this someday.</i>

1500
01:21:03,734 --> 01:21:07,112
<i>I wanted to impart
a little dad advice.</i>

1501
01:21:07,196 --> 01:21:09,073
<i>Rule one:</i>

1502
01:21:10,324 --> 01:21:13,410
<i>Take care of your mom.
She's your best friend.</i>

1503
01:21:14,161 --> 01:21:16,914
<i>Rule two: Bullies are cowards.</i>

1504
01:21:17,581 --> 01:21:19,083
<i>Hit back.</i>

1505
01:21:19,166 --> 01:21:20,501
<i>Rule three:</i>

1506
01:21:20,584 --> 01:21:24,755
<i>You can be kind and
strong at the same time.</i>

1507
01:21:26,715 --> 01:21:30,677
<i>Rule four: Don't trust
the Network... ever.</i>

1508
01:21:32,054 --> 01:21:33,430
<i>And rule five:</i>

1509
01:21:36,141 --> 01:21:38,060
<i>You remember...</i>

1510
01:21:38,143 --> 01:21:40,312
<i>your dada loves you a whole lot.</i>

1511
01:21:42,147 --> 01:21:45,609
<i>I'll be looking out for
you. No matter what.</i>

1512
01:21:46,235 --> 01:21:47,528
Ha!

1513
01:21:47,611 --> 01:21:50,280
I knew it was you.

1514
01:21:50,364 --> 01:21:52,741
Devil. Murderer!

1515
01:21:52,825 --> 01:21:55,410
- You stay away from my Eltie.
- Ma'am?

1516
01:21:55,494 --> 01:21:56,787
You savage!

1517
01:21:56,870 --> 01:21:57,913
Wait! Mom!

1518
01:21:57,996 --> 01:22:01,375
You'll never eat puppies again.

1519
01:22:01,458 --> 01:22:02,918
Mom, no! No!

1520
01:22:03,001 --> 01:22:04,586
Mom, it's okay! He's a friend!

1521
01:22:04,670 --> 01:22:06,171
Eltie, no!

1522
01:22:06,255 --> 01:22:07,965
Ma'am, ma'am!

1523
01:22:08,048 --> 01:22:11,301
If you press that button,
the NCG will come in firing.

1524
01:22:11,385 --> 01:22:14,221
Okay? They will not care who
gets caught in the cross fire.

1525
01:22:14,304 --> 01:22:15,430
It will be a bloodbath.

1526
01:22:17,182 --> 01:22:20,936
We don't need every Goon in the
state coming through that door, right?

1527
01:22:23,230 --> 01:22:24,606
Don't.

1528
01:22:26,483 --> 01:22:28,837
<i>Network Community Guard.
What crime would you like to report?</i>

1529
01:22:28,861 --> 01:22:32,197
Ben Richards just
broke into my home!

1530
01:22:32,281 --> 01:22:33,198
<i>Okay, stay where you are.</i>

1531
01:22:33,282 --> 01:22:34,366
- Why?
- Ma saw you.

1532
01:22:34,449 --> 01:22:36,160
We got to get going.

1533
01:22:36,243 --> 01:22:38,829
I just need five minutes of fun
with these guys before we do.

1534
01:22:39,705 --> 01:22:40,831
Fun?

1535
01:22:40,914 --> 01:22:42,833
Grab your stuff!
I'll get the 'zines!

1536
01:22:46,211 --> 01:22:48,505
They're coming to get you!

1537
01:22:50,299 --> 01:22:52,217
You're not listening.
It's dangerous!

1538
01:22:52,301 --> 01:22:53,468
No!

1539
01:22:53,552 --> 01:22:55,345
Mom, get in the safe room!

1540
01:22:55,429 --> 01:22:57,264
No, Eltie, I want to see him die!

1541
01:22:57,347 --> 01:23:00,225
You hear that, welf?
You're gonna die!

1542
01:23:01,977 --> 01:23:03,020
They're here.

1543
01:23:18,785 --> 01:23:19,828
Mom!

1544
01:23:19,912 --> 01:23:22,831
He's here! Richards is in the hall!

1545
01:23:22,915 --> 01:23:25,709
- Mom!
- Kill him!

1546
01:23:25,792 --> 01:23:27,544
- Come on!
- No! Let me go!

1547
01:23:27,628 --> 01:23:29,755
No! I don't want to miss it!

1548
01:23:29,838 --> 01:23:32,382
I want to see!

1549
01:23:32,466 --> 01:23:33,466
Let's move!

1550
01:23:33,508 --> 01:23:35,302
This way. Come on.

1551
01:23:35,385 --> 01:23:39,389
Yo, dip shits! You
shot up the wrong hall!

1552
01:23:39,473 --> 01:23:41,225
We're over here!

1553
01:23:49,775 --> 01:23:50,901
Here we go.

1554
01:23:50,984 --> 01:23:53,237
Are you crazy? We don't
have time to play games!

1555
01:23:53,320 --> 01:23:54,404
Oh, yes, we do.

1556
01:23:54,488 --> 01:23:57,616
Fastest the Hunters ever arrived
on-scene was 4 minutes 30 seconds.

1557
01:23:57,699 --> 01:23:59,493
We'll be long gone by then.

1558
01:24:00,994 --> 01:24:02,704
Go! Go! Move!

1559
01:24:02,788 --> 01:24:03,848
♪ <i>The police in New York City</i> ♪

1560
01:24:03,872 --> 01:24:06,792
Yoo-hoo! Hey, big boys!

1561
01:24:06,875 --> 01:24:09,544
♪ <i>They chased a boy
Right through the park</i> ♪

1562
01:24:11,672 --> 01:24:14,174
♪ <i>And in a case of
mistaken identity</i> ♪

1563
01:24:15,926 --> 01:24:18,303
♪ <i>They put a bullet
through his heart</i> ♪

1564
01:24:20,055 --> 01:24:23,392
♪ <i>Heart breaker, heart breaker</i> ♪

1565
01:24:24,935 --> 01:24:26,575
♪ <i>She stuck the pins
right in her heart</i> ♪

1566
01:24:26,603 --> 01:24:28,480
I like my bacon extra crispy!

1567
01:24:28,563 --> 01:24:30,190
- We got to go, man!
- Follow me.

1568
01:24:30,274 --> 01:24:31,316
Shit!

1569
01:24:31,400 --> 01:24:33,443
♪ <i>A pain maker</i> ♪

1570
01:24:34,736 --> 01:24:35,946
Shit!

1571
01:24:38,865 --> 01:24:40,409
Come on!

1572
01:24:40,492 --> 01:24:41,868
♪ <i>Doo doo doo doo doo doo</i> ♪

1573
01:24:41,952 --> 01:24:44,579
♪ <i>I wanna tear that world apart</i> ♪

1574
01:24:45,914 --> 01:24:47,514
♪ <i>Doo doo, doo doo
doo doo doo doo doo</i> ♪

1575
01:24:48,166 --> 01:24:49,501
Yeah!

1576
01:24:49,584 --> 01:24:50,669
Let's go!

1577
01:24:50,752 --> 01:24:52,671
♪ <i>I wanna tear this world apart</i> ♪

1578
01:24:52,754 --> 01:24:54,506
Whoo!

1579
01:24:54,589 --> 01:24:58,093
♪ <i>Heart breaker, heart breaker</i> ♪

1580
01:24:58,176 --> 01:24:59,636
Why are we upstairs?

1581
01:24:59,720 --> 01:25:00,863
♪ <i>You stole the love
right out my heart</i> ♪

1582
01:25:00,887 --> 01:25:02,806
Go! Go!

1583
01:25:02,889 --> 01:25:06,184
♪ <i>Heart breaker, heart breaker</i> ♪

1584
01:25:11,440 --> 01:25:13,108
Yes! Yes!

1585
01:25:13,191 --> 01:25:16,278
Elton! Why are we upstairs?

1586
01:25:16,361 --> 01:25:18,822
♪ <i>I wanna tear your world apart</i> ♪

1587
01:25:19,865 --> 01:25:21,074
For this!

1588
01:25:22,242 --> 01:25:25,078
You brought us up here so
you could slide down a pole?

1589
01:25:25,162 --> 01:25:29,708
I brought us up here so
we could slide down a pole!

1590
01:25:29,791 --> 01:25:30,917
♪ <i>Oh, yeah</i> ♪

1591
01:25:36,506 --> 01:25:39,718
See? Four minutes flat.
Told you we'd be long gone.

1592
01:25:39,801 --> 01:25:43,513
Long gone? We are still
in the goddamn house!

1593
01:25:45,057 --> 01:25:46,266
Not for long!

1594
01:25:57,819 --> 01:25:59,154
Tactical flashlight.

1595
01:25:59,237 --> 01:26:00,739
- Pretty powerful.
- Yeah.

1596
01:26:03,075 --> 01:26:04,242
Come on.

1597
01:26:13,251 --> 01:26:15,504
I'm gonna sever your
Achilles and drag you outside.

1598
01:26:15,587 --> 01:26:18,590
Chief wants to end your
run in person, on camera.

1599
01:26:59,798 --> 01:27:02,175
Don't let him answer that!

1600
01:27:03,301 --> 01:27:04,886
<i>Still there?</i>

1601
01:27:04,970 --> 01:27:07,222
- Yeah.
<i>- Put him on.</i>

1602
01:27:07,305 --> 01:27:08,306
It's for you.

1603
01:27:12,018 --> 01:27:14,896
<i>Ah! There he is.</i>

1604
01:27:14,980 --> 01:27:17,274
<i>Incredible work,
Mr. Richards. You are killing it.</i>

1605
01:27:17,357 --> 01:27:21,445
Killing it? People are dying,
you fucking psychopath!

1606
01:27:22,487 --> 01:27:25,449
If you can fake everything, why
don't you just fake the whole show?

1607
01:27:25,532 --> 01:27:27,200
<i>Believe me, we have tried.</i>

1608
01:27:27,284 --> 01:27:30,745
<i>But humans bring that
special unpredictable spark.</i>

1609
01:27:30,829 --> 01:27:33,331
<i>The audience lives for
these happy accidents.</i>

1610
01:27:33,415 --> 01:27:34,958
<i>- A little advice?</i>
- I'll pass.

1611
01:27:35,041 --> 01:27:37,335
Make sure my family gets the money.

1612
01:27:37,419 --> 01:27:38,962
<i>Richards, don't go.</i>

1613
01:27:39,921 --> 01:27:44,217
<i>You can still win this game,
but you have to play it smart.</i>

1614
01:27:44,301 --> 01:27:46,219
<i>I just sent a rover
into that tunnel.</i>

1615
01:27:47,679 --> 01:27:51,141
<i>Now finish off that Hunter
and wait for my cue to exit.</i>

1616
01:27:51,224 --> 01:27:53,518
You want me to off
one of your own guys?

1617
01:27:53,602 --> 01:27:55,645
<i>It's all good Free-Vee.</i>

1618
01:27:55,729 --> 01:27:59,524
<i>Okay, on you in five... four...</i>

1619
01:27:59,608 --> 01:28:01,193
<i>three...</i>

1620
01:28:01,276 --> 01:28:02,736
<i>two...</i>

1621
01:28:02,819 --> 01:28:04,196
<i>one.</i>

1622
01:28:04,279 --> 01:28:05,739
<i>And action.</i>

1623
01:28:14,498 --> 01:28:15,498
Get in!

1624
01:28:16,791 --> 01:28:18,835
- Floor it!
- What about the doors?

1625
01:28:21,087 --> 01:28:22,506
Oh, shit!

1626
01:28:24,633 --> 01:28:25,633
Hold on!

1627
01:28:29,346 --> 01:28:31,026
- Where are we going?
- Down the dirt road.

1628
01:28:32,641 --> 01:28:34,351
- They're all dirt roads!
- There!

1629
01:28:34,434 --> 01:28:35,685
- The trail!
- Okay.

1630
01:28:40,899 --> 01:28:43,068
Son of a... bitch.

1631
01:28:45,487 --> 01:28:47,697
Cross the bridge and drop me off.

1632
01:28:47,781 --> 01:28:49,866
I can slow them down.

1633
01:28:50,909 --> 01:28:52,744
Take back roads to the shelter.

1634
01:28:52,827 --> 01:28:54,871
Survival is the win!

1635
01:28:59,876 --> 01:29:00,876
This way!

1636
01:29:05,549 --> 01:29:06,883
Take this map.

1637
01:29:06,967 --> 01:29:10,053
Dad's bunker is in
the middle of the forest.

1638
01:29:10,136 --> 01:29:13,223
Remember, Richards...
you're the initiator.

1639
01:29:29,489 --> 01:29:30,740
<i>Green light on Richards.</i>

1640
01:29:39,874 --> 01:29:42,210
It's the end of your run, Richards.

1641
01:29:44,337 --> 01:29:45,337
Fuck it.

1642
01:29:47,299 --> 01:29:49,092
I am the initiator.

1643
01:30:17,621 --> 01:30:19,289
The thrill of the hunt.

1644
01:30:19,998 --> 01:30:21,207
Can you feel it?

1645
01:30:23,043 --> 01:30:25,253
<i>Your heart beats faster.</i>

1646
01:30:25,337 --> 01:30:28,465
<i>Bright red blood pumps
adrenaline through your veins.</i>

1647
01:30:29,215 --> 01:30:31,134
This game is no game.

1648
01:30:32,552 --> 01:30:35,430
<i>Life and death are on the line.</i>

1649
01:30:35,513 --> 01:30:38,266
Can you feel it, Mr. Richards?

1650
01:30:38,350 --> 01:30:41,561
Congratulations.
You took out a Hunter.

1651
01:30:42,562 --> 01:30:44,439
Now it's down to four of them.

1652
01:30:44,522 --> 01:30:48,652
<i>Plus every citizen
of this great nation.</i>

1653
01:30:48,735 --> 01:30:51,321
"Hundred and five
paces west of big rock.

1654
01:30:51,404 --> 01:30:53,573
Bunker's dug into the hill."

1655
01:30:55,033 --> 01:30:56,701
Well, shit.

1656
01:30:56,785 --> 01:30:59,204
Can you smell it?

1657
01:31:00,080 --> 01:31:02,332
<i>The acrid stink of fear</i>

1658
01:31:02,415 --> 01:31:06,002
<i>as the prey animal realizes
he's surrounded by predators.</i>

1659
01:31:06,086 --> 01:31:09,673
Reality sinks in as
he scurries to hide,

1660
01:31:09,756 --> 01:31:12,300
<i>desperately hoping to survive.</i>

1661
01:31:12,384 --> 01:31:16,513
<i>But deep down, he already
knows it's too late, because...</i>

1662
01:31:17,097 --> 01:31:19,057
this is America, goddamn it,

1663
01:31:19,140 --> 01:31:21,559
and we don't put
up with no bullshit!

1664
01:31:22,811 --> 01:31:26,523
<i>Bloodlust is our
birthright. Set it free.</i>

1665
01:31:27,107 --> 01:31:29,067
Richards chose this path,

1666
01:31:29,150 --> 01:31:31,611
and it's up to you to
show him where it ends.

1667
01:31:32,362 --> 01:31:35,490
<i>Keep your eyes open so
you can see the terror in his,</i>

1668
01:31:35,573 --> 01:31:38,243
and hunt him down!

1669
01:31:38,326 --> 01:31:41,621
Hunt him down! Hunt him down!

1670
01:31:41,705 --> 01:31:44,582
Hunt him down! Hunt him down!

1671
01:31:44,666 --> 01:31:47,335
Hunt him down! Hunt him down!

1672
01:31:47,419 --> 01:31:50,004
Hunt him down! Hunt him down!

1673
01:32:06,146 --> 01:32:09,274
I see, yeah.

1674
01:32:09,357 --> 01:32:12,235
I see! Wow!

1675
01:32:12,318 --> 01:32:14,362
Look, it's Dada.

1676
01:32:14,446 --> 01:32:15,989
Yeah!

1677
01:32:16,740 --> 01:32:19,075
Look. Look.

1678
01:32:26,708 --> 01:32:28,960
I told you I'd get
you out of there.

1679
01:32:31,087 --> 01:32:34,132
People on this show
never come back.

1680
01:32:56,404 --> 01:32:59,866
<i>This is a message for Killian.</i>

1681
01:33:01,326 --> 01:33:03,703
<i>Hey, Dan.</i>

1682
01:33:03,787 --> 01:33:05,663
<i>I'm starting to get
how this game works.</i>

1683
01:33:07,707 --> 01:33:10,794
<i>It's not about me
winning or losing.</i>

1684
01:33:11,544 --> 01:33:13,797
<i>It's about your ratings.</i>

1685
01:33:13,880 --> 01:33:15,965
<i>About how much chaos I can cause.</i>

1686
01:33:17,425 --> 01:33:20,303
<i>I'm taking this thing
all the way to the end.</i>

1687
01:33:20,386 --> 01:33:23,598
<i>And I am done playing
defense, I promise you that.</i>

1688
01:33:23,681 --> 01:33:24,974
<i>So here's the deal.</i>

1689
01:33:25,558 --> 01:33:28,978
<i>I will see my family again.</i>

1690
01:33:29,062 --> 01:33:31,564
<i>And as long as they
keep getting paid,</i>

1691
01:33:31,648 --> 01:33:34,025
<i>you can put whoever
you want in front of me.</i>

1692
01:33:34,108 --> 01:33:36,569
<i>I will run through all of them.</i>

1693
01:33:38,196 --> 01:33:40,365
<i>I know you fight dirty.</i>

1694
01:33:40,448 --> 01:33:42,992
<i>Well, guess what,
you son of a bitch.</i>

1695
01:33:43,076 --> 01:33:46,663
<i>I'm from Slumside. Let's
throw the rule book out.</i>

1696
01:33:46,746 --> 01:33:49,666
<i>Here's to mutually
profitable annihilation.</i>

1697
01:33:49,749 --> 01:33:51,626
<i>- You want a show?</i>
- Damn it.

1698
01:33:51,709 --> 01:33:53,086
<i>I'll give you a show.</i>

1699
01:33:53,169 --> 01:33:54,754
Whoo-hoo!

1700
01:33:54,838 --> 01:33:58,591
♪ <i>Americanos, Americanos</i> ♪

1701
01:33:58,675 --> 01:33:59,968
<i>Sing it, girl.</i>

1702
01:34:00,051 --> 01:34:03,513
<i>Yes! Here we go! Let's do this!</i>

1703
01:34:03,596 --> 01:34:06,116
<i>We interrupt</i> The Americanos <i>for a
live update from</i> The Running Man.

1704
01:34:06,140 --> 01:34:07,308
<i>Boring!</i>

1705
01:34:07,392 --> 01:34:09,561
- Who even likes this show?
<i>- The poors. Duh.</i>

1706
01:34:09,644 --> 01:34:10,520
Zaza!

1707
01:34:10,603 --> 01:34:12,289
<i>They're the only ones
dense enough to think it's real.</i>

1708
01:34:12,313 --> 01:34:13,690
I know. It's so fake.

1709
01:34:13,773 --> 01:34:14,941
Stop!

1710
01:34:16,442 --> 01:34:17,711
<i>What is happening? Are you okay?</i>

1711
01:34:17,735 --> 01:34:19,445
<i>Oh, my God!</i>

1712
01:34:19,529 --> 01:34:22,198
<i>What's happening, Amelia?
Don't hurt her, please!</i>

1713
01:34:22,282 --> 01:34:24,284
Go, go! Take it off autopilot!

1714
01:34:25,451 --> 01:34:27,370
Drive! Take the
next back road north.

1715
01:34:27,453 --> 01:34:29,581
I can't. My power's on empty.

1716
01:34:29,664 --> 01:34:32,625
<i>Your battery is 93% charged. Nice!</i>

1717
01:34:32,709 --> 01:34:34,836
Those Goons are going to frag us

1718
01:34:34,919 --> 01:34:39,090
if you don't back
this car up right now!

1719
01:34:40,967 --> 01:34:42,468
Whoa!

1720
01:34:43,970 --> 01:34:45,889
They're here!

1721
01:34:45,972 --> 01:34:48,224
<i>Your car is damaged.
Your car is damaged.</i>

1722
01:34:49,434 --> 01:34:51,144
Go, go! Keep it moving!

1723
01:34:53,229 --> 01:34:54,564
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

1724
01:34:56,232 --> 01:34:57,233
Left!

1725
01:35:03,656 --> 01:35:05,116
Jesus!

1726
01:35:07,035 --> 01:35:09,704
Now I see why you people
need self-driving cars.

1727
01:35:09,787 --> 01:35:11,414
<i>Recalculating.</i>

1728
01:35:16,920 --> 01:35:20,673
Keep it pointed north.
All the way to the border.

1729
01:35:22,508 --> 01:35:26,095
Go ahead. Say what you got to say.

1730
01:35:26,179 --> 01:35:27,722
Why?

1731
01:35:27,805 --> 01:35:29,891
So you can go crazy and kill me?

1732
01:35:30,808 --> 01:35:31,935
No.

1733
01:35:32,018 --> 01:35:35,021
You have one
minute to speak freely.

1734
01:35:35,104 --> 01:35:38,441
How do you live with yourself? Hmm?

1735
01:35:38,524 --> 01:35:41,235
You dare sit there
and criticize my driving?

1736
01:35:41,319 --> 01:35:44,238
Tell me how to operate my own car?

1737
01:35:44,322 --> 01:35:46,199
I am a member of society!

1738
01:35:46,282 --> 01:35:48,326
You disgust me!

1739
01:35:49,452 --> 01:35:51,120
You abandoned that starving baby,

1740
01:35:51,204 --> 01:35:53,456
that horrible wife of yours.

1741
01:35:53,539 --> 01:35:54,749
So you can what?

1742
01:35:54,832 --> 01:35:57,460
Kill people for money?

1743
01:35:57,543 --> 01:35:59,629
And you only kill the best people!

1744
01:35:59,712 --> 01:36:01,756
The people who protect us from...

1745
01:36:01,839 --> 01:36:03,633
from welfs like you!

1746
01:36:03,716 --> 01:36:06,260
And that's not a word I use!

1747
01:36:11,724 --> 01:36:13,309
That is my family.

1748
01:36:15,436 --> 01:36:17,605
Our number finally
came up for the park.

1749
01:36:17,689 --> 01:36:20,942
I watched Cathy try ice
cream for the first time.

1750
01:36:22,902 --> 01:36:25,321
That was the best day of my life.

1751
01:36:25,405 --> 01:36:27,281
So yeah, you're right.

1752
01:36:27,365 --> 01:36:30,118
The show is so fake.

1753
01:36:30,201 --> 01:36:32,328
Not the bullets. Not the death.

1754
01:36:32,412 --> 01:36:34,372
Just the part that
makes people like you

1755
01:36:34,455 --> 01:36:37,250
think you're better
than people like us.

1756
01:36:37,333 --> 01:36:40,003
Let me ask you something.
How much was that scarf?

1757
01:36:40,086 --> 01:36:41,546
Huh?

1758
01:36:41,629 --> 01:36:45,633
More than the meds my daughter
needed when she was dying of the flu?

1759
01:36:45,717 --> 01:36:47,218
The flu!

1760
01:36:47,301 --> 01:36:51,472
That is a human life
hanging around your neck!

1761
01:36:53,099 --> 01:36:55,643
But you seem to be doing fine.

1762
01:36:55,727 --> 01:36:57,603
Who can blame
you? It's a nice scarf.

1763
01:36:58,730 --> 01:37:00,106
I'm not a bad person.

1764
01:37:00,189 --> 01:37:02,108
No, do not start crying.

1765
01:37:02,191 --> 01:37:04,485
I will shoot us both
if you start crying.

1766
01:37:04,569 --> 01:37:06,612
Cry when it's over.

1767
01:37:06,696 --> 01:37:08,489
When will that be?

1768
01:37:08,573 --> 01:37:10,783
Shit.

1769
01:37:10,867 --> 01:37:13,828
<i>Yielding for an
emergency vehicle. Nice!</i>

1770
01:37:13,911 --> 01:37:16,873
- Disable it! Disable it! Do not pull over!
- I don't know how!

1771
01:37:16,956 --> 01:37:19,751
<i>Yielding in 100 feet.</i>

1772
01:37:20,710 --> 01:37:23,212
<i>- 50 feet.</i>
- Pull over!

1773
01:37:23,296 --> 01:37:25,631
<i>In 20 feet.</i>

1774
01:37:25,715 --> 01:37:29,093
<i>You have successfully
yielded. Nice!</i>

1775
01:37:32,055 --> 01:37:33,765
Shit.

1776
01:37:33,848 --> 01:37:35,266
Oh, hey, Richards.

1777
01:37:35,349 --> 01:37:39,353
You've been pulled over by
the Rustic Rock Mulisha Boyz.

1778
01:37:39,437 --> 01:37:43,399
We're here securing our homestead
in the name of the Network.

1779
01:37:43,483 --> 01:37:45,693
Don't worry, lady.
We're the good guys.

1780
01:37:45,777 --> 01:37:47,737
Just step out of the car.

1781
01:37:47,820 --> 01:37:49,489
You'll be safe with us.

1782
01:37:49,572 --> 01:37:51,074
It's him we want.

1783
01:37:55,036 --> 01:37:56,579
Just go.

1784
01:38:06,798 --> 01:38:08,800
What the fuck is happening?

1785
01:38:09,675 --> 01:38:13,262
The producers just killed
Network militia instead of me.

1786
01:38:13,346 --> 01:38:16,557
They wouldn't do that. Those men
were just trying to protect me from you.

1787
01:38:16,641 --> 01:38:20,061
What is it gonna take for
you to get I'm not the bad guy?

1788
01:38:25,399 --> 01:38:28,611
Take the car. Just drive
away. I don't want to hurt you.

1789
01:38:28,694 --> 01:38:30,905
You think they're gonna let
you walk after seeing that?

1790
01:38:30,988 --> 01:38:33,324
- You're on the show now.
- No, I'm not!

1791
01:38:33,407 --> 01:38:36,702
<i>Richards lives. And this
time he's got a hostage.</i>

1792
01:38:36,786 --> 01:38:40,248
<i>Amelia Williams, a 27-year-old
realtor from Bangor, Maine.</i>

1793
01:38:40,331 --> 01:38:43,751
<i>Help me! He's got a gun!</i>

1794
01:38:44,669 --> 01:38:46,087
Welcome to <i>The Running Man.</i>

1795
01:38:46,170 --> 01:38:48,548
<i>Help me, please!</i>

1796
01:38:48,631 --> 01:38:50,842
<i>The crisis continues,</i>

1797
01:38:50,925 --> 01:38:53,685
<i>as Miss Williams's gray Alpine heads
north on Rustic Rock Siding Road.</i>

1798
01:38:53,719 --> 01:38:57,765
<i>The hostage situation has triggered
the NCG to go into full tactical alert.</i>

1799
01:38:57,849 --> 01:38:59,267
<i>Help me!</i>

1800
01:38:59,350 --> 01:39:00,410
- Turn it off.
<i>- He's got a gun!</i>

1801
01:39:00,434 --> 01:39:01,853
Just turn it off!

1802
01:39:01,936 --> 01:39:04,230
<i>Miss Williams was
carjacked and kidnapped by...</i>

1803
01:39:06,691 --> 01:39:09,235
Richards lives! Whoo!

1804
01:39:09,318 --> 01:39:11,529
Yeah!

1805
01:39:11,612 --> 01:39:13,614
Richards lives! Richards lives!

1806
01:39:13,698 --> 01:39:15,324
Go, Richards!

1807
01:39:16,367 --> 01:39:18,536
- Unbelievable.
- Goons ahead!

1808
01:39:18,619 --> 01:39:20,496
Watch yourself!

1809
01:39:20,580 --> 01:39:22,373
Yeah, it's a circus all right.

1810
01:39:22,456 --> 01:39:24,083
So they're just gonna
keep filming us?

1811
01:39:24,167 --> 01:39:27,587
If a Runner gets good
ratings, they let him run.

1812
01:39:27,670 --> 01:39:29,463
- Richards lives!
- Oh, God.

1813
01:39:29,547 --> 01:39:31,299
Is that a blockade?

1814
01:39:31,382 --> 01:39:35,887
Oh, shit. All right. If we play
our parts, they'll let us pass.

1815
01:39:35,970 --> 01:39:38,681
Oh, shit, shit, shit.

1816
01:39:38,764 --> 01:39:40,183
Richards lives!

1817
01:39:40,266 --> 01:39:42,810
Okay. Just keep driving.
They're not gonna shoot.

1818
01:39:42,894 --> 01:39:44,520
How do you know?

1819
01:39:44,604 --> 01:39:47,315
'Cause they're gonna wait
for the show to start. Do it live.

1820
01:39:47,398 --> 01:39:50,359
- Do what live?
- Kill me.

1821
01:39:52,486 --> 01:39:54,572
- Richards lives!
- Open up!

1822
01:39:54,655 --> 01:39:56,324
They're waving us through.

1823
01:39:56,407 --> 01:39:58,367
Yo, Richards! We got you, man!

1824
01:39:58,451 --> 01:40:00,578
Why are they cheering for
you when I'm the hostage?

1825
01:40:01,996 --> 01:40:03,247
Unbelievable.

1826
01:40:04,290 --> 01:40:05,666
Amelia?

1827
01:40:05,750 --> 01:40:07,210
Will you give me the gun?

1828
01:40:08,377 --> 01:40:11,297
Why not? You're obviously the hero.

1829
01:40:12,423 --> 01:40:14,133
Trust me.

1830
01:40:14,217 --> 01:40:16,761
I don't think we're
gonna need this anymore.

1831
01:40:18,012 --> 01:40:20,348
<i>Record and Report.
State your claim.</i>

1832
01:40:20,431 --> 01:40:23,142
<i>Oh, my God. I just
saw Ben Richards.</i>

1833
01:40:23,226 --> 01:40:26,646
<i>I'm sorry, wait. I am Ben Richards.</i>

1834
01:40:26,729 --> 01:40:29,190
<i>If you don't want to be
the reason Amelia dies,</i>

1835
01:40:29,273 --> 01:40:31,442
<i>get this message to Killian.</i>

1836
01:40:31,525 --> 01:40:33,236
<i>Do what he says, please!</i>

1837
01:40:33,319 --> 01:40:34,987
<i>You heard the lady.</i>

1838
01:40:35,071 --> 01:40:39,283
Richards lives! Richards
lives! Richards lives!

1839
01:40:39,367 --> 01:40:41,577
Richards lives! Richards lives!

1840
01:41:01,722 --> 01:41:04,100
Go, Richards!

1841
01:41:05,226 --> 01:41:08,229
Go, Richards!

1842
01:41:08,312 --> 01:41:13,025
Before you murder us, make up
some bullshit why it had to be done,

1843
01:41:13,943 --> 01:41:16,946
look at all these people
who know the truth.

1844
01:41:17,029 --> 01:41:20,074
Are you willing to kill all
of them? Because I am.

1845
01:41:21,826 --> 01:41:25,246
I'm holding onto this
bullhorn with my right hand.

1846
01:41:25,329 --> 01:41:28,416
My left hand is in my front pouch,

1847
01:41:28,499 --> 01:41:32,169
wrapped around twelve
pounds of Black Irish.

1848
01:41:35,923 --> 01:41:39,135
When I used to work
in Network Public Utility,

1849
01:41:39,218 --> 01:41:40,636
you'd get these two-ton fatbergs,

1850
01:41:40,720 --> 01:41:43,306
take less than a
gram to blow those up.

1851
01:41:43,389 --> 01:41:44,682
Twelve pounds.

1852
01:41:44,765 --> 01:41:47,101
It'll vaporize everything
in a half-mile radius.

1853
01:41:53,816 --> 01:41:56,110
Bull... shit.

1854
01:41:56,193 --> 01:42:00,740
BFE-20 is the most highly
regulated industrial explosive.

1855
01:42:00,823 --> 01:42:04,368
And you haven't even set
foot in a state that sells it.

1856
01:42:04,452 --> 01:42:06,287
I guess Molie didn't
tell you everything.

1857
01:42:06,370 --> 01:42:10,624
I got my finger stuck in the
detonator ring and it's on half-cock.

1858
01:42:10,708 --> 01:42:12,168
So...

1859
01:42:12,251 --> 01:42:16,255
I want one of those big
fancy Flying-V airplanes.

1860
01:42:16,339 --> 01:42:19,884
I want two autochutes handed to
Amelia at the bottom of the ramp.

1861
01:42:19,967 --> 01:42:22,303
If the chutes are sabotaged,

1862
01:42:22,386 --> 01:42:24,347
if you make any sudden moves,

1863
01:42:24,430 --> 01:42:25,931
if you don't back those trucks up

1864
01:42:26,015 --> 01:42:28,976
and let me on that
tarmac right fucking now,

1865
01:42:29,060 --> 01:42:31,812
you won't even hear it go boom.

1866
01:42:31,896 --> 01:42:35,399
I'll just see you in hell
and laugh in your face.

1867
01:42:35,483 --> 01:42:36,609
You got one minute.

1868
01:42:41,489 --> 01:42:43,657
Shouldn't take long.

1869
01:42:43,741 --> 01:42:46,077
He's got a direct line to the boss.

1870
01:42:48,162 --> 01:42:49,538
Last chance to run.

1871
01:42:50,748 --> 01:42:52,833
No.

1872
01:42:52,917 --> 01:42:55,836
You made me feel
like I'm the bad guy.

1873
01:42:57,129 --> 01:42:58,923
Now I have to prove I'm not.

1874
01:42:59,965 --> 01:43:01,509
Why do you give
a shit what I think?

1875
01:43:03,219 --> 01:43:05,096
You're not the one
I'm trying to prove it to.

1876
01:43:08,057 --> 01:43:09,517
So what's our plan?

1877
01:43:09,600 --> 01:43:10,810
<i>Let him through.</i>

1878
01:43:10,893 --> 01:43:13,270
<i>I'm gonna convince them
your handbag is a bomb</i>

1879
01:43:13,354 --> 01:43:16,399
<i>long enough to bail
out over Canada.</i>

1880
01:43:16,982 --> 01:43:18,317
<i>They'll never let me win,</i>

1881
01:43:18,401 --> 01:43:21,654
<i>so I'm gonna slip out the back
door and wait out the clock.</i>

1882
01:43:21,737 --> 01:43:23,423
<i>We just have to keep
the audience entertained</i>

1883
01:43:23,447 --> 01:43:26,492
<i>until that jet crosses the border.</i>

1884
01:43:26,575 --> 01:43:28,494
What if they call your bluff?

1885
01:43:28,577 --> 01:43:32,206
You make sure they know
it's real. Get scared, freak out.

1886
01:43:32,289 --> 01:43:35,835
Curse, scream, call me
the worst names possible.

1887
01:43:37,711 --> 01:43:39,588
Just remember, everything bad,

1888
01:43:40,673 --> 01:43:42,341
it's all good Free-Vee.

1889
01:43:43,884 --> 01:43:46,303
<i>Act terrified when McCone
hands you the chutes.</i>

1890
01:43:46,387 --> 01:43:48,431
<i>I won't have to act.</i>

1891
01:43:48,514 --> 01:43:53,144
<i>He grabs his gun, you'll
know it's time to go off.</i>

1892
01:44:01,235 --> 01:44:03,737
So, you think you're the guy

1893
01:44:03,821 --> 01:44:06,115
who stops me from
seeing my daughter again?

1894
01:44:06,198 --> 01:44:08,033
Show starts at 8:00.

1895
01:44:08,117 --> 01:44:09,326
Get on the plane.

1896
01:44:09,410 --> 01:44:11,704
Only if you take your mask off.

1897
01:44:11,787 --> 01:44:12,997
Audience will love it.

1898
01:44:13,080 --> 01:44:14,915
Keep dreaming.

1899
01:44:14,999 --> 01:44:17,251
- <i>Do what he says.</i>
- No copy.

1900
01:44:17,334 --> 01:44:19,128
<i>Do what he says. Take it off.</i>

1901
01:44:33,225 --> 01:44:35,269
There he is.

1902
01:44:40,983 --> 01:44:43,527
Come on, show starts at 8:00.

1903
01:44:47,907 --> 01:44:50,576
<i>Welcome aboard, Mr. Richards,</i>

1904
01:44:50,659 --> 01:44:54,371
<i>to the Net-Air Flying-V
Luxury Jetliner,</i>

1905
01:44:54,455 --> 01:44:56,749
<i>the ultimate in private travel.</i>

1906
01:44:56,832 --> 01:44:59,084
<i>With state-of-the-art
safety features,</i>

1907
01:44:59,168 --> 01:45:03,130
<i>this is first-class
comfort taken sky high.</i>

1908
01:45:03,214 --> 01:45:07,635
<i>So sit back and enjoy the
most relaxing flight of your life.</i>

1909
01:45:07,718 --> 01:45:10,054
Oh, welcome aboard, Mr. Richards.

1910
01:45:10,137 --> 01:45:11,764
I'm Captain Holloway.

1911
01:45:11,847 --> 01:45:14,475
You'll excuse me if I
don't shake your hand.

1912
01:45:15,434 --> 01:45:17,061
That's First Officer Duninger

1913
01:45:17,144 --> 01:45:19,647
and Navigation Officer
Donahue to your left.

1914
01:45:20,648 --> 01:45:21,848
Looks like you're missing one.

1915
01:45:24,527 --> 01:45:27,488
Hey, Captain, how many
lavatories are on this rust bucket?

1916
01:45:27,571 --> 01:45:29,949
- Four.
- Six.

1917
01:45:30,032 --> 01:45:32,159
Why don't you check
them all for stowaways?

1918
01:45:32,243 --> 01:45:34,161
Anyone sneaks up on me,

1919
01:45:34,245 --> 01:45:35,704
it's gonna be a real short ride.

1920
01:45:35,788 --> 01:45:37,831
So, where are we headed tonight?

1921
01:45:39,041 --> 01:45:42,086
Plot a route over the richest
homes from here to Canada.

1922
01:45:42,836 --> 01:45:44,004
Fly as low as you can.

1923
01:45:44,088 --> 01:45:46,090
Let me know when we're
ten minutes from the border.

1924
01:45:46,173 --> 01:45:48,175
As you wish.

1925
01:45:58,894 --> 01:46:01,230
<i>The seat belt sign is now off.</i>

1926
01:46:01,313 --> 01:46:03,023
<i>Feel free to move about the cabin.</i>

1927
01:46:03,107 --> 01:46:06,235
Hey, Richards. Six
minutes to showtime.

1928
01:46:06,318 --> 01:46:08,797
You should get that last meal before
they clear me to blow your head off

1929
01:46:08,821 --> 01:46:10,489
in front of a couple
billion people.

1930
01:46:10,573 --> 01:46:12,116
Oh, yeah?

1931
01:46:12,199 --> 01:46:14,660
You should really put some
makeup on before the show starts.

1932
01:46:14,743 --> 01:46:16,870
Fuck the show! Let's go.

1933
01:46:16,954 --> 01:46:19,790
- You want to go? We can all go right now!
- No, no, no! Just stop!

1934
01:46:19,873 --> 01:46:22,001
Do it! Do it, tough guy!

1935
